## 2. Date-only: backend `DATE` columns

### The contract

`PersonalEvent.date`, `Appointment.scheduled_date`, and any other
field typed as `string` representing a calendar day MUST be
`"YYYY-MM-DD"`. Never an ISO timestamp, never a `Date` object
JSON-serialized to `"2026-04-21T04:00:00.000Z"`.

### Producer side

Form inputs already produce `"YYYY-MM-DD"`. If you compute a date,
construct it from local Y/M/D components, not via `.toISOString()`
(which can shift the day east of UTC).

### Consumer side

When mapping a backend response, use `toCalendarDayKey(value)` from
`@/src/utils/resource-calendar-mapping` to defensively normalize.

### Why this exists

`node-pg` returns Postgres `DATE` columns as JavaScript `Date` objects
constructed at local-midnight. JSON-serializing them produces an ISO
timestamp that downstream code uses as a `Map` key against
`"YYYY-MM-DD"` strings → silent zero matches. The backend now
normalizes at the repository boundary
(`personal-event.repository.ts → toDateOnlyString`), but the contract
must hold at every layer.

